	<ThingDef ParentName="LeatherBase">
		<defName>Leather_Beet</defName>
		<label>Beet Chitin</label>
		<description>The skin and innards of a Beet, tanned and dried. On Old Earth flora, chitin comprised the cell walls of fungi, not plants. On animals, chitin was a component of the thick, armored skin of insects, including the fearsome Insectoids that terrorize the Rim. Beets, of course, are not plants or fungi, even though they share such characteristics. /n /n The resilliance of a Beet's body makes Beet Chitin capable of being a construction material and fearsome armor against blunt attacks! It can be used anywhere wood can be used! However, it does not insulate, is very flammable, and is notably brittle as a building material. Armor utilizing Beet Chitin easily cracks when sharp, direct stabs are applied to it. It feels like beeswax to the touch.</description>
		<graphicData>
			<color>(210,170,110)</color>
		</graphicData>
		<soundDrop>Wood_Drop</soundDrop>
		<statBases Inherit="False">
			<MarketValue>2.17</MarketValue>
			<Flammability>1.75</Flammability>
			<MaxHitPoints>40</MaxHitPoints>
			<Mass>0.02</Mass>
			<SharpDamageMultiplier Inherit="False">0.18</SharpDamageMultiplier>
			<BluntDamageMultiplier Inherit="False">1.05</BluntDamageMultiplier>
			<StuffPower_Insulation_Cold Inherit="False">0</StuffPower_Insulation_Cold>
			<StuffPower_Insulation_Heat Inherit="False">0</StuffPower_Insulation_Heat>
			<StuffPower_Armor_Sharp>0.1</StuffPower_Armor_Sharp>
			<StuffPower_Armor_Blunt>1.05</StuffPower_Armor_Blunt>
			<StuffPower_Armor_Heat>0</StuffPower_Armor_Heat>
		</statBases>
		<stuffProps Inherit="False">
			<color>(210,170,110)</color>
			<commonality>0.03</commonality>
			<stuffAdjective>Beet</stuffAdjective>
			<categories>
				<li>Woody</li>
				<li>Leathery</li>
				
				<!-- Mod support -->
				<li MayRequire="biomesteam.biomescore">BMT_ChitinStuff</li>
				<li MayRequire="sarg.rimbees">RB_Waxy</li>
			</categories>
			<constructEffect>ConstructWood</constructEffect>
			<appearance>Smooth</appearance>
			<!-- <appearance MayRequire="sera.apinialienrace">Hive</appearance> -->
			<soundImpactStuff>BulletImpact_Wood</soundImpactStuff>
			<soundMeleeHitSharp>MeleeHit_Wood</soundMeleeHitSharp>
			<soundMeleeHitBlunt>MeleeHit_Wood</soundMeleeHitBlunt>
			<statOffsets>
				<WorkToBuild>-50</WorkToBuild>
				<!-- <MaxHitPoints>-30</MaxHitPoints> -->
				<Beauty>-0.5</Beauty>
			</statOffsets>
			<statFactors>
				<MaxHitPoints>0.18</MaxHitPoints>
				<DoorOpenSpeed>2</DoorOpenSpeed>
				<WorkToBuild>0.9</WorkToBuild> <!-- Ten percent faster -->
			</statFactors>
		</stuffProps>
		<healthAffectsPrice>false</healthAffectsPrice>
		<thingCategories Inherit="False">
			<li>ResourcesRaw</li>
			<li>Leathers</li>
		</thingCategories>
		<terrainAffordanceNeeded>Light</terrainAffordanceNeeded>
	</ThingDef>
  
  <ThingDef ParentName="LeatherBase">
    <defName>Gnome_Cloth</defName>
    <label>Gnome poppy fiber</label>
	<description>Fibers spun from the roots and seed pods of the Gnome Root poppy. Versatile as cloth and leather. Gnomes, a subspecies of man, use these to keep warm in the winter akin to industrial hemp fibers. It is exceptionally effective against cold, but not heat, and is extremely long lasting, albeit terrible in terms of armor (especially blunt armor). Do not let it get near an open flame. \n \n Gnomes have long fed their animals this substance, because Gnome Root poppy fibers are edible in the same way kibble is: no man wants to eat them.</description>
	<socialPropernessMatters>true</socialPropernessMatters>
    <graphicData>
      <color>(34,139,34)</color>
    </graphicData>
		<thingCategories Inherit="False">
			<li>Textiles</li>
			<li>Wools</li>
			<li>Leathers</li>
			<li>PlantMatter</li>
		</thingCategories>
		<statBases>
			<MarketValue>0.4</MarketValue>
			<Nutrition>0.35</Nutrition>
			<Mass>0.01</Mass>
			<Flammability>1.5</Flammability>
			<StuffPower_Insulation_Cold>27</StuffPower_Insulation_Cold>
			<StuffPower_Insulation_Heat>2</StuffPower_Insulation_Heat>
			<StuffPower_Armor_Sharp>0.33</StuffPower_Armor_Sharp>
			<StuffPower_Armor_Blunt>0.1</StuffPower_Armor_Blunt>
		</statBases>
		<stackLimit>500</stackLimit>
		<stuffProps>
			<categories Inherit="False">
				<li>Fabric</li>
				<li>Leathery</li>
			</categories>
			<color>(34,139,34)</color>
			<commonality>0.05</commonality>
			<stuffAdjective>poppy</stuffAdjective>
			<statFactors>
				<MaxHitPoints>1.9</MaxHitPoints>
			</statFactors>
			<statOffsets>
				<Flammability>0.5</Flammability>
			</statOffsets>
		</stuffProps>
		<ingestible>
			<preferability>DesperateOnlyForHumanlikes</preferability>
			<foodType Inherit="False">Kibble</foodType>
			<tasteThought>AteKibble</tasteThought>
			<optimalityOffsetHumanlikes>-100</optimalityOffsetHumanlikes>
			<optimalityOffsetFeedingAnimals>10</optimalityOffsetFeedingAnimals>
			<tableDesired>false</tableDesired>
		</ingestible>
  </ThingDef>
  
